,"mental health journal","silly posts","my art","cats of cohost","cornhub","nihongo no jikan"],"askSettings":{"enabled":true,"allowAnon":true,"requireLoggedInAnon":true},"contactCard":[],"deleteAfter":null,"isSelfProject":null}},{"comment":{"commentId":"65a5fc8e-8c25-4565-acce-3552e8014f5f","postedAtISO":"2022-12-27T23:32:28.510Z","deleted":false,"body":"I never saw this one - by the time I was growing up and they were doing reruns some twenty years later the smoking wouldn't fly - but dang, that really is a Tom and Jerry episode cut down to three minutes with some math tossed in, isn't it? Not a bad setup.\n\nI will say the 'digits add up' thing maybe shoulda been mentioned to only work up to 9x10, but oh well. They've already established the idea of breaking down x\\*y for y\u003E10 to x\\*10+x\\*(y-10), so kids should be able to figure it out","children":[{"comment":{"commentId":"ed908910-18c3-4753-a2df-e846a83b38f5","postedAtISO":"2022-12-30T18:31:17.785Z","deleted":false,"body":"It works above that too! You just have to keep taking the digit sum until you get down to one digit!\n\nFor example, 11 * 9 = 99; 9 + 9 = 18; 1 + 8 = 9. And above too: 13 * 9 = 117; 1 + 1 + 7 = 9.\n\nYou can basically summarize it as adding up the digits will either give 9 or a multiple of 9. Which works for multiples of 3 too! 3 * 13 = 39; 3 + 9 = 12; 1 + 2 = 3.\n\nWhich then multiples of 6 are just the even multiples of 3, so that works too!","children":[],"postId":596292,"inReplyTo":"65a5fc8e-8c25-4565-acce-3552e8014f5f","hasCohostPlus":true,"hidden":false},"canInteract":"allowed","canEdit":"not-allowed","canHide":"not-allowed","poster":{"projectId":8810,"handle":"chimerror","displayName":"Chimerelda E. Error, layabout","dek":"I'm Kitty (and so can you!)","description":"Just a leopard from Seattle who sometimes makes games when she remembers to.","avatarURL":"https:\u002F\u002Fstaging.cohostcdn.org\u002Favatar\u002F8810-da0b5564-bf08-4296-b3b7-2f7f01c8333e-profile.png","avatarPreview